GGPLOT GRAPHING

library(ggmap)
## Warning: package 'ggmap' was built under R version 3.4.4
## Loading required package: ggplot2
library(ggplot2)
# I will be using an R dataset package named "quakes". 
# This dataset includes the location of seismic events of in Puerto Rico; from the UPRM database.

PR_Earthquakes = read.table("PREarthquakes.csv", header=TRUE,sep=",", stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
View(PR_Earthquakes)
names(PR_Earthquakes)
## [1] "Magnitude" "Agency"    "Latitude"  "Longitude" "Depth"     "Felt"     
## [7] "Region"
str(PR_Earthquakes)
## 'data.frame':    50 obs. of  7 variables:
##  $ Magnitude: num  3.66 3.83 3.47 3.61 3.68 3.58 3.9 3.46 3.56 3.64 ...
##  $ Agency   : chr  "PRSN" "PRSN" "PRSN" "PRSN" ...
##  $ Latitude : num  18.2 18.1 19 18 18.8 ...
##  $ Longitude: num  -67.9 -68.8 -64.9 -68.7 -68.7 ...
##  $ Depth    : int  123 156 26 101 144 28 9 126 29 33 ...
##  $ Felt     : chr  "No" "No" "No" "No" ...
##  $ Region   : chr  "MONA PASSAGE" "EASTERN DOMINICAN REPUBLIC" "SOMBRERO SEISMIC ZONE" "EASTERN DOMINICAN REPUBLIC" ...
# Now we I am going to create a new dataset that only includes the information that 
# I will be using (the longitude, latitude and the magnitude) for my maps. 

Earthquakes = PR_Earthquakes[c("Longitude", "Latitude", "Magnitude")]
head(Earthquakes) #To verify we will look to the first part of the data. 
##   Longitude Latitude Magnitude
## 1  -67.8873  18.1948      3.66
## 2  -68.7711  18.1026      3.83
## 3  -64.9226  18.9903      3.47
## 4  -68.7251  17.9721      3.61
## 5  -68.6516  18.7591      3.68
## 6  -64.8130  19.2351      3.58
PRMap = get_map(location='puerto rico', zoom = 7, maptype = "satellite", source = 'google', color = 'color')
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=puerto+rico&zoom=7&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=satellite&language=en-EN&sensor=false
## Information from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=puerto%20rico&sensor=false
#Once the get_map function has found the map I will combine the ggmap package with 
#the ggplot2 package. 

ggmap(PRMap) + geom_point(aes(x=Longitude, y=Latitude, show_guide = TRUE, colour= Magnitude),
                  data= Earthquakes, alpha = 0.99, na.rm=TRUE) + scale_color_gradient(low="yellow", high = "red")
## Warning: Ignoring unknown aesthetics: show_guide

Lets change some arguments

#You can also change the zoom, color of the map, color of magnitude scale, size of the dots
PRMap2 = get_map(location='puerto rico', zoom = 8, maptype = "roadmap", source = 'google', color = 'color')
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=puerto+rico&zoom=8&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=roadmap&language=en-EN&sensor=false
## Information from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=puerto%20rico&sensor=false
ggmap(PRMap2) + geom_point(aes(x=Longitude, y=Latitude, show_guide = TRUE, colour= Magnitude),
                  data= Earthquakes, alpha = 0.99, size=3, na.rm=TRUE) + scale_color_gradient(low="green", high = "black") 
## Warning: Ignoring unknown aesthetics: show_guide
